555
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:24,810
Back then,

556
00:29:25,160 --> 00:29:26,160
a small burial pit

557
00:29:26,830 --> 00:29:30,680
from Empress Dowager Bo's South Mausoleum,
located to the east of Yin Village,

558
00:29:30,680 --> 00:29:33,070
was excavated in a rescue operation.

559
00:29:34,200 --> 00:29:37,110
In the 1980s, two veteran archaeologists

560
00:29:37,550 --> 00:29:39,280
conducted systematic surveys

561
00:29:39,510 --> 00:29:41,270
and measurements

562
00:29:42,350 --> 00:29:44,070
of the 11 Western Han Mausoleums,

563
00:29:44,070 --> 00:29:47,800
laying a solid foundation
for the future archaeological research

564
00:29:48,070 --> 00:29:50,330
of the Western Han Imperial Mausoleums.

565
00:29:50,680 --> 00:29:52,000
After 2003,

566
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:53,350
researchers from

567
00:29:53,350 --> 00:29:56,160
the Qinchuan
Archaeological Research Institute

568
00:29:56,790 --> 00:30:00,160
discovered the grand tomb in Yin Village,

569
00:30:00,640 --> 00:30:03,040
along with surrounding outer burial pits,

570
00:30:03,350 --> 00:30:05,030
stone enclosures, and other features
during their exploration.

571
00:30:05,030 --> 00:30:05,890
These findings

572
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:09,310
brought the relationship between
the Dou Mausoleum, Phoenix Mountain,

573
00:30:09,310 --> 00:30:10,970
and the Yin Village grand tomb

574
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:14,880
into the academic spotlight,

575
00:30:15,510 --> 00:30:16,770
sparking discussions

576
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:18,640
about the exact location

577
00:30:18,960 --> 00:30:21,290
of Emperor Taizong of Han's Zi Mausoleum.

578
00:30:24,750 --> 00:30:25,280
May I ask,

579
00:30:25,350 --> 00:30:27,720
will the main tomb of Zi Mausoleum
continue to be excavated?

580
00:30:27,720 --> 00:30:30,110
Under our country's
cultural heritage policy,

581
00:30:30,110 --> 00:30:34,440
the excavation of ancient imperial tombs

582
00:30:34,640 --> 00:30:36,720
is generally not permitted.

583
00:30:37,480 --> 00:30:38,310
Archaeology

584
00:30:39,640 --> 00:30:41,030
is not treasure hunting.

585
00:30:41,030 --> 00:30:43,160
We can't simply excavate
every tomb we discover.

586
00:30:43,160 --> 00:30:44,720
What we choose to excavate now

587
00:30:44,720 --> 00:30:46,790
is based on current research needs.

588
00:30:46,830 --> 00:30:49,700
This is a legacy
we should leave to future generations.

589
00:30:49,700 --> 00:30:51,360
When the technology is ready,

590
00:30:51,550 --> 00:30:53,550
and when their research demands it,

591
00:30:53,890 --> 00:30:54,960
then the time will be right
for excavation.

592
00:30:54,960 --> 00:30:55,890
Okay, thank you.

593
00:30:59,750 --> 00:31:01,750
If I may add to
what the director just said,

594
00:31:01,750 --> 00:31:03,450
our top priority right now

595
00:31:03,480 --> 00:31:06,200
is to protect
these mausoleums and cultural relics.

596
00:31:06,200 --> 00:31:08,160
Our archaeological team
hopes that in the future,

597
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:09,480
we'll be able to build a site museum

598
00:31:09,480 --> 00:31:10,830
on the Bailu Plain

599
00:31:11,480 --> 00:31:12,550
-to showcase...
-Director Yan.

600
00:31:12,550 --> 00:31:14,170
And preserve the discoveries
from the Zi Mausoleum...

601
00:31:14,170 --> 00:31:14,550
Director Yan.

602
00:31:14,550 --> 00:31:16,920
And Empress Dowager Bo's South Mausoleum.

603
00:31:16,920 --> 00:31:18,110
It will also help more people

604
00:31:18,110 --> 00:31:19,920
gain a deeper understanding
of our Chinese culture.

605
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:20,850
Okay, thank you.

606
00:31:24,210 --> 00:31:27,270
Then may I ask, have the stolen artifacts
from the Zi Mausoleum been recovered?

607
00:31:27,270 --> 00:31:28,070
Wait a moment.

608
00:31:29,680 --> 00:31:31,830
I'll take this question.

609
00:31:32,930 --> 00:31:37,530
The stolen artifacts from the Zi Mausoleum
have been recovered one after another.

610
00:31:37,590 --> 00:31:38,030
Bravo!

611
00:31:41,070 --> 00:31:41,580
Bravo!

612
00:32:13,920 --> 00:32:14,450
Mr. Fang,

613
00:32:16,310 --> 00:32:18,170
are you familiar with this place?

614
00:32:18,380 --> 00:32:21,180
The black pottery figurines
were unearthed here.

615
00:32:22,110 --> 00:32:23,170
Let me correct you.

616
00:32:24,830 --> 00:32:27,690
The black pottery figurines
were stolen from here.

617
00:32:27,750 --> 00:32:28,550
You're right.

618
00:32:29,790 --> 00:32:31,120
No one knows better than I do

619
00:32:31,120 --> 00:32:32,840
how they were dug up

620
00:32:33,640 --> 00:32:34,960
and sold overseas.

621
00:32:36,750 --> 00:32:37,880
If it weren't for me,

622
00:32:38,110 --> 00:32:39,310
how would foreigners

623
00:32:39,830 --> 00:32:42,960
come to understand
the rich history of Chinese culture?

624
00:32:43,110 --> 00:32:45,310
Taking our ancestors' treasures

625
00:32:46,380 --> 00:32:47,910
and selling them overseas,

626
00:32:48,270 --> 00:32:49,900
then letting foreigners show them off,

627
00:32:49,900 --> 00:32:52,560
yet acting like
that's something to be proud of?

628
00:32:53,680 --> 00:32:54,880
Don't be so harsh.

629
00:32:55,830 --> 00:32:58,030
Without me, what would you be studying?

630
00:32:58,830 --> 00:33:00,560
Even the probing shovel you use

631
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:02,830
was invented by tomb raiders.

632
00:33:04,200 --> 00:33:05,000
That's right.

633
00:33:06,780 --> 00:33:08,580
It was invented by tomb raiders.

634
00:33:09,510 --> 00:33:10,920
But it's just a tool.

635
00:33:11,920 --> 00:33:13,880
A knife is a harmless kitchen utensil
when used for cooking,

636
00:33:13,880 --> 00:33:16,140
but it becomes a weapon when used to harm.

637
00:33:17,110 --> 00:33:20,080
We use probing shovels
to uncover and verify history,

638
00:33:20,080 --> 00:33:21,200
while you use them

639
00:33:21,590 --> 00:33:23,470
to turn our intact Chinese culture

640
00:33:23,470 --> 00:33:26,340
into something broken and unrecognizable.

641
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:40,400
If I hadn't brought
the black pottery figurines to light,

642
00:33:40,400 --> 00:33:41,830
you would never have known

643
00:33:41,830 --> 00:33:43,160
where Zi Mausoleum was.

644
00:33:44,070 --> 00:33:45,350
I am the herald.

645
00:33:45,750 --> 00:33:46,960
I am the pioneer.

646
00:33:47,180 --> 00:33:49,380
I am the first to discover Zi Mausoleum.

647
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:54,880
What are you laughing at?

648
00:33:54,880 --> 00:33:57,740
I'm laughing at
your ignorance and shamelessness.

649
00:33:57,960 --> 00:33:59,640
Years ago, we already began

650
00:33:59,640 --> 00:34:02,440
excavating the
Western Han Imperial Mausoleums.

651
00:34:03,030 --> 00:34:04,960
Even if the grand tomb in Yin Village
hadn't been found,

652
00:34:04,960 --> 00:34:06,470
our plan was to

653
00:34:07,240 --> 00:34:09,280
explore Phoenix Mountain anyway,

654
00:34:09,600 --> 00:34:12,300
and we would have still confirmed
there were no remains beneath it.

655
00:34:12,300 --> 00:34:13,100
Yin Village

656
00:34:14,590 --> 00:34:15,719
and the Zi Mausoleum

657
00:34:16,550 --> 00:34:18,610
would have come to light regardless.

658
00:34:19,440 --> 00:34:20,570
Relying on you guys?

659
00:34:21,280 --> 00:34:23,610
By the time you're done,
it'll be too late.

660
00:34:23,670 --> 00:34:26,670
You've poured
countless man-hours and resources in,

661
00:34:26,710 --> 00:34:28,739
yet still haven't completed
a single tomb after all these years.

662
00:34:28,739 --> 00:34:30,030
With just one shovel,

663
00:34:30,360 --> 00:34:31,820
I cracked the whole thing.

664
00:34:31,840 --> 00:34:33,380
Because you're in it for the money.

665
00:34:33,380 --> 00:34:34,190
We're not.

666
00:34:35,230 --> 00:34:37,920
For generations,
archaeologists have worked tirelessly,

667
00:34:37,920 --> 00:34:40,550
pursuing knowledge with care

668
00:34:40,880 --> 00:34:42,840
and exploring with painstaking dedication.

669
00:34:42,840 --> 00:34:43,280
Why?

670
00:34:45,960 --> 00:34:47,510
Because what we're uncovering

671
00:34:47,510 --> 00:34:49,770
is the very backbone of Chinese history,

672
00:34:49,880 --> 00:34:51,880
the profound depth
of Chinese civilization.

673
00:34:51,880 --> 00:34:54,610
We can't afford to be careless,
not even a little.

674
00:34:56,630 --> 00:34:59,230
You've destroyed
countless cultural relics,

675
00:34:59,550 --> 00:35:01,550
yet you still call yourself a herald

676
00:35:02,590 --> 00:35:03,400
and a pioneer.

677
00:35:04,320 --> 00:35:06,250
You're not ashamed but proud of it.

678
00:35:07,440 --> 00:35:08,900
It's utterly ridiculous.

679
00:35:30,740 --> 00:35:31,400
Mu Jianhui,

680
00:35:31,960 --> 00:35:33,160
you're under arrest.

681
00:35:54,360 --> 00:35:55,000
Shulan,

682
00:35:56,940 --> 00:35:58,140
I've implicated you.

683
00:36:06,060 --> 00:36:08,260
I'll wait for you to come back, Jianhui.

684
00:37:06,710 --> 00:37:07,320
Who are you?

685
00:37:07,320 --> 00:37:07,920
Police!

686
00:37:09,710 --> 00:37:10,770
What are you doing?

687
00:37:13,960 --> 00:37:14,960
What's your name?

688
00:37:15,590 --> 00:37:16,280
Hu Qingye.

689
00:37:36,010 --> 00:37:41,420
[Qinchuan City Public Security Bureau]

690
00:37:44,250 --> 00:37:45,090
[Yusai]

691
00:37:45,090 --> 00:37:50,230
♪ Do you know ♪

692
00:37:50,230 --> 00:37:50,760
How much?

693
00:37:52,150 --> 00:37:53,280
One meter...

694
00:37:55,840 --> 00:37:56,250
One meter and seventy-three centimeters.

695
00:37:56,250 --> 00:38:01,070
♪ How many bends the Yellow River has? ♪

696
00:38:01,070 --> 00:38:02,190
This data

697
00:38:02,630 --> 00:38:04,090
has been mostly gathered.

698
00:38:05,110 --> 00:38:06,370
It's nearly complete.

699
00:38:09,150 --> 00:38:09,680
Mr. Fang,

700
00:38:10,360 --> 00:38:11,960
the weather is quite pleasant today.

701
00:38:11,960 --> 00:38:13,420
The wind isn't too strong,

702
00:38:13,800 --> 00:38:14,760
but the days

703
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:16,860
are getting shorter and shorter.

704
00:38:17,670 --> 00:38:18,840
♪ So many bends, oh ♪

705
00:38:18,840 --> 00:38:20,070
Time flies,

706
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:22,730
and it's almost New Year again.

707
00:38:23,150 --> 00:38:23,750
Oh, right.

708
00:38:24,040 --> 00:38:24,590
♪ So many boats, hey ♪

709
00:38:24,590 --> 00:38:26,800
The New Year holiday
is just around the corner.

710
00:38:26,800 --> 00:38:28,800
You've got a 10-day break this time.

711
00:38:28,880 --> 00:38:31,540
Don't you want to go back
to Qinchuan for a visit?

712
00:38:32,320 --> 00:38:34,580
Let's get this year's report done first.

713
00:38:35,270 --> 00:38:37,440
♪ On the boats ♪

714
00:38:37,440 --> 00:38:37,970
Mr. Fang,

715
00:38:40,320 --> 00:38:41,630
I've always wondered.

716
00:38:41,630 --> 00:38:43,760
♪ So many poles, hey ♪

717
00:38:43,760 --> 00:38:44,320
Well...

718
00:38:46,070 --> 00:38:47,650
Why didn't you stay in Qinchuan back then?

719
00:38:47,650 --> 00:38:57,070
♪ So many boatmen,
oh, steering the boats ♪

720
00:38:57,070 --> 00:38:58,660
Just as I told you before,

721
00:38:59,840 --> 00:38:59,950
this Great Wall project in Yusai

722
00:38:59,950 --> 00:39:01,400
♪ So many boatmen,
oh, steering the boats ♪

723
00:39:01,400 --> 00:39:03,260
has always been a knot in my heart.

724
00:39:04,070 --> 00:39:05,470
Mr. Zan didn't finish it,

725
00:39:06,400 --> 00:39:07,860
so I want to see it through.

726
00:39:10,630 --> 00:39:12,230
The grand tomb in Yin Village

727
00:39:12,670 --> 00:39:14,270
has troubled me for 10 years.

728
00:39:15,000 --> 00:39:16,730
Now that the mystery is solved,

729
00:39:17,630 --> 00:39:19,220
cultural preservation and excavation

730
00:39:19,220 --> 00:39:20,280
are progressing well.

731
00:39:20,280 --> 00:39:22,610
They need me here more than anywhere else.

732
00:39:23,960 --> 00:39:24,290
Yeah.

733
00:39:26,960 --> 00:39:27,420
Well...

734
00:39:29,360 --> 00:39:30,880
Is Ms. Luo doing well?

735
00:39:31,880 --> 00:39:32,480
Are you...

736
00:39:33,280 --> 00:39:35,080
Are you willing to part with her?

737
00:39:38,800 --> 00:39:39,670
On her end,

738
00:39:44,630 --> 00:39:45,840
everything must be going smoothly.

739
00:39:45,840 --> 00:39:46,630
I trust her.

740
00:39:48,110 --> 00:39:49,030
Each archaeologist

741
00:39:49,030 --> 00:39:51,000
has their own responsibilities.

742
00:39:52,730 --> 00:39:53,960
Back then, Ms. Luo gave up

743
00:39:53,960 --> 00:39:55,360
the Lv Family Tomb for me.

744
00:39:58,760 --> 00:40:00,220
That was a huge sacrifice.

745
00:40:01,190 --> 00:40:02,760
Though she never said it aloud,

746
00:40:02,760 --> 00:40:04,320
everyone understands.

747
00:40:05,320 --> 00:40:07,400
A project is like our own child.

748
00:40:07,550 --> 00:40:10,680
Sometimes, it's even more important
than our own lives.

749
00:40:10,800 --> 00:40:11,110
Yes.

750
00:40:12,440 --> 00:40:15,170
If you ask me
whether I'm willing to part with her,

751
00:40:15,330 --> 00:40:16,800
of course I'm not.

752
00:40:17,760 --> 00:40:19,370
But I can't be that selfish.

753
00:40:19,840 --> 00:40:20,240
Right?

754
00:40:22,400 --> 00:40:23,070
Mr. Bai!

755
00:40:24,110 --> 00:40:24,570
Coming.

756
00:40:24,920 --> 00:40:25,250
Here.

757
00:40:26,070 --> 00:40:27,190
You... you go ahead with your work.

758
00:40:27,190 --> 00:40:27,630
Alright.

759
00:40:27,630 --> 00:40:28,360
Coming!

760
00:40:53,230 --> 00:40:54,190
Archaeology

761
00:40:54,840 --> 00:40:56,510
can make a nation's history

762
00:40:56,510 --> 00:40:58,510
clearer and more transparent.

763
00:40:59,510 --> 00:41:01,170
Archaeological discoveries

764
00:41:01,190 --> 00:41:02,670
can fill in the gaps

765
00:41:02,670 --> 00:41:05,130
missing from historical records and texts.

766
00:41:05,920 --> 00:41:07,480
They piece together

767
00:41:07,630 --> 00:41:08,960
every trace of history,

768
00:41:09,840 --> 00:41:12,400
reconstructing the complete story
of Chinese civilization's development—

769
00:41:12,400 --> 00:41:14,110
making it accessible to everyone,

770
00:41:14,110 --> 00:41:15,770
and sharing it with the world.

771
00:41:16,030 --> 00:41:17,800
Striking the ground
to mend the tapestry of history—

772
00:41:17,800 --> 00:41:20,060
that's the true meaning of archaeology.

773
00:41:20,150 --> 00:41:22,030
Every word we archaeologists say,

774
00:41:22,030 --> 00:41:23,360
every judgment we make,

775
00:41:23,510 --> 00:41:24,670
could determine

776
00:41:25,280 --> 00:41:26,440
whether a piece of history

777
00:41:26,440 --> 00:41:27,440
and civilization

778
00:41:27,710 --> 00:41:29,510
is understood correctly or not.

779
00:42:00,330 --> 00:42:01,000
Pig Three.

780
00:42:03,190 --> 00:42:05,970
♪ Time leaves its marks, worn and faded ♪

781
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:08,000
♪ Like the wind that weaves and wanders ♪

782
00:42:08,180 --> 00:42:10,150
♪ Free yet lonely ♪

783
00:42:10,990 --> 00:42:12,840
♪ How much silence ♪

784
00:42:13,030 --> 00:42:14,890
♪ Quietly speaks ♪

785
00:42:15,010 --> 00:42:18,920
♪ The past's clarity and muddle unfold ♪

786
00:42:19,280 --> 00:42:22,020
♪ Watch the sunset over the plains ♪

787
00:42:22,040 --> 00:42:24,040
♪ See the stars that shimmer bright ♪

788
00:42:24,060 --> 00:42:26,310
♪ Behold the fireworks
lighting the night ♪

789
00:42:26,340 --> 00:42:28,810
♪ The heart firmly holds
its truth and right ♪

790
00:42:29,080 --> 00:42:31,080
♪ How could one ever miss such sights? ♪

791
00:42:31,340 --> 00:42:32,640
♪ The lights ♪

792
00:42:32,670 --> 00:42:37,600
♪ Their glow sweeps away all doubts ♪

793
00:42:38,490 --> 00:42:40,310
♪ These hands ♪

794
00:42:40,340 --> 00:42:42,340
♪ Have passed through time ♪

795
00:42:42,360 --> 00:42:45,980
♪ Holding tight ♪

796
00:42:46,380 --> 00:42:50,860
♪ That fiery blood
pulses deep within our veins ♪

797
00:42:51,000 --> 00:42:54,950
♪ Carrying the heartbeat
of dreams through time ♪

798
00:42:56,130 --> 00:42:58,130
♪ That is our belief ♪

799
00:42:58,150 --> 00:42:58,890
♪ And we will never back down ♪

